SIMPLE: monogamy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monogamy
<hw>Mo*nog"a*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>monogamia</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>monogamie</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Single marriage; marriage with but one person, husband
or wife, at the same time; -- opposed to <contr>polygamy</contr>. Also,
one marriage only during life; -- opposed to
<contr>deuterogamy</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>State of being paired with a
single mate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monogastric</ent>⟦br⟧
